# Foodie — environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
#   cp .env.example .env   (Mac/Linux)
#   copy .env.example .env  (Windows)
#
# .env is gitignored — never commit real keys.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Flask
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Secret key signs session cookies. Use a long random string in production.
# SECRET_KEY=dev-secret-not-for-production

# Database URL. Default points at the db service in Docker Compose.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://app:app@db:5432/app

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Edamam Recipe Search API  (REQUIRED for live recipe search)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Without these keys /recipes/search will always return an "upstream error"
# flash instead of real results.  The app still runs — auth, meal plan, and
# scale all work without them.
#
# How to get free keys (takes ~2 minutes):
#   1. Go to https://developer.edamam.com/
#   2. Click "Get Started" → sign up for a free account
#   3. Go to Dashboard → Applications → "Create a new application"
#   4. Choose "Recipe Search API" (free tier: 10 000 requests / month)
#   5. Copy the Application ID and Application Key shown on the app page
#
# Paste them here (remove the leading #):
# EDAMAM_APP_ID=your_app_id_here
# EDAMAM_APP_KEY=your_app_key_here
